President Donald J. Trump is taking action to eliminate unnecessary and outdated regulations in order to stimulate the economy and create jobs. The president believes that an excessive amount of regulations has cost the country trillions of dollars, millions of jobs, and has negatively impacted various industries. Trump's administration is committed to reducing burdensome red tape and will continue their efforts to deregulate in the coming fiscal year. These measures aim to bring about real change and deliver positive results for the American people.